- "Severity level" refers to the level of impact or damage caused by a cybersecurity incident; 
- "Extent of damage" is measured by the number of corrupted servers and pages; 
- "Speed of the fastest hacker" is determined by their typing speed in words per minute (WPM).

- Incident response teams are groups of professionals who respond to and manage the aftermath of security incidents or breaches.; 
- A higher average typing speed might imply more skilled or experienced hackers, but this could also depend on various factors such as the complexity of the incidents and the hackers' familiarity with the systems compromised.; 
- The total number of servers corrupted can indicate the severity of the incidents handled by each team.
